19:09.725 --> 19:10.406
So what do we do?

19:10.486 --> 19:19.236
We've got to focus, focus on what we can control and surrender what we can't control.

19:21.038 --> 19:24.001
So let's think about the things that we should control in our lives.

19:24.061 --> 19:25.042
We should control

19:25.154 --> 19:31.641
our choices, our values, our self-discipline, our reactions, our emotions.

19:31.721 --> 19:45.216
We can control those things and God wants us to, but the things that we can't control, the things that are happening around the world and governments and the wars and the things that get us angry and frustrated and the injustices and all the things that happen.

19:45.637 --> 19:50.162
And yes, we should use our voice, but we also, we need to surrender.

19:51.586 --> 19:57.092
because some of the things that we're trying to control weren't meant for us to control, they were meant for us to surrender.

20:00.276 --> 20:09.547
And dropping the weight of trying to control someone in the natural actually gives room for God to move in the spiritual.

20:09.567 --> 20:13.011
And for some of those times we mean this is really difficult.

20:13.632 --> 20:18.898
Because if you were kind of born as a command and control, you like to control things.

20:19.298 --> 20:25.985
God says, I made you that way and there's certain things I want you to do, but on the things that you can't, I want you to surrender them.

20:28.408 --> 20:37.698
And some of us are trying to control our parents, our kids, our bosses, trying to control everything God sent today, I just simply want you to surrender them.

20:39.801 --> 20:42.704
Control what I've given you power to control and surrender what you can.

20:44.406 --> 20:48.050
The third way that I choose to let go of is

20:49.186 --> 20:50.647
my temptation to settle.

20:52.810 --> 20:57.094
Fear of the future, control and temptation to settle.

20:58.355 --> 21:04.942
I turned 47 last month and these temptations can slowly start creeping in.

21:06.324 --> 21:10.688
You can start inviting little thoughts to start growing in your mind.

21:10.708 --> 21:16.594
So often when we're confronted with setbacks or difficult situations or bad reports,

21:16.706 --> 21:19.250
We don't see the thing that we've been praying for, the miracle.

21:19.830 --> 21:22.474
We can buckle over and start settling.

21:23.455 --> 21:24.977
So, well, it didn't happen last year.

21:25.017 --> 21:26.700
It didn't happen the five years before.

21:27.040 --> 21:28.883
Maybe it's just not going to happen.

21:30.665 --> 21:35.973
And settling, if you want to write this down, settling is simply compromise mingled with disappointment.

21:37.855 --> 21:42.802
So we get disappointed and we just think, you know what, I'll just settle.

21:44.610 --> 21:53.179
I spoke to a gentleman in the last service, he said that his son, his son had gone for 500 jobs, but 500 job applications in.

21:53.199 --> 21:56.763
And he called him, he said that, I just can't do it.

21:57.023 --> 21:58.185
I'm just not cut out for work.

21:58.965 --> 22:00.047
His dad said, don't give up.

22:01.648 --> 22:02.649
Don't give up, try again.

22:03.510 --> 22:05.352
Two or three applications later, he got a job.

22:08.115 --> 22:09.357
Two or three applications later.

22:09.657 --> 22:09.857
Why?

22:10.177 --> 22:14.482
Because you can quit just before your breakthrough.

22:14.626 --> 22:16.689
You can quit just before your miracle.

22:18.611 --> 22:21.274
You know, five years now, we're believing for a Christian school.

22:22.375 --> 22:23.337
No real breakthroughs.

22:24.378 --> 22:27.442
And the enemy over the Christmas period, he said, John, just lay it down.

22:28.423 --> 22:28.964
Just give up.

22:30.385 --> 22:36.973
It's easy to say no, but when you ain't sin, and I don't know your situation, but you do know my, it's easy just to go, you know, I'll just settle.

22:37.814 --> 22:38.555
Look, we've built this.

22:39.617 --> 22:40.418
We'll just keep going.

22:42.460 --> 22:44.082
But something in me was rising up.

22:44.898 --> 22:47.261
This week, something in me was saying, hey, come on.

22:47.942 --> 22:49.444
Don't compromise what God's giving you.

22:50.245 --> 22:52.227
Don't compromise the dream in your heart.

22:52.247 --> 22:53.729
Don't settle for disappointment.

22:53.969 --> 22:55.391
Don't settle for second best.

22:55.631 --> 22:59.135
For some of you, do not settle for what God has spoken to you about.

22:59.155 --> 23:01.378
If God said he's going to do it, he's going to do it.

23:01.578 --> 23:02.499
It might take time.

23:02.760 --> 23:03.621
It might take months.

23:03.681 --> 23:04.742
It might even take years.

23:04.962 --> 23:06.644
But I refuse to settle.

23:07.686 --> 23:08.507
I refuse to.

23:09.548 --> 23:12.692
Now, here's the thing about selling, and I need everybody to write this down.

23:12.712 --> 23:14.514
I'll take a note on it.

23:14.690 --> 23:16.632
It's one of the most important things I'm going to say today.

23:17.053 --> 23:20.056
Settle once and you'll find it very easy to settle again.

23:21.938 --> 23:24.761
The moment you start settling once, you'll settle again.

23:26.583 --> 23:28.725
I felt the Holy Spirit give me a little bit of a kick.

23:29.967 --> 23:31.028
He said, John, don't settle.

23:31.989 --> 23:32.810
We're not going to settle.

23:35.993 --> 23:39.237
Don't resign yourself to the job that you don't really like.

23:39.417 --> 23:41.660
I believe that God has got a better job out there for you.

23:42.280 --> 23:43.922
We've got to keep hoping and believing.

23:45.090 --> 23:51.016
Now, in this passage in verse two, it says, fixing our eyes on Jesus.

23:51.116 --> 23:54.500
I've never, I've read this a hundred times, but I've never, this never jumped at me.

23:54.880 --> 23:55.741
The pioneer.

23:57.923 --> 23:59.505
Jesus was a pioneer.

24:02.307 --> 24:05.150
And I said to God, God, I want to catch the pioneer spirit.

24:06.532 --> 24:07.973
I want to pioneer spirit again.

24:07.993 --> 24:08.914
What do pioneers do?

24:08.954 --> 24:10.015
They keep moving forward.

24:10.216 --> 24:10.976
They don't settle.

24:11.156 --> 24:12.658
They say, give me another mountain.

24:13.986 --> 24:15.688
Do not quit.

24:15.948 --> 24:17.410
Someone needs to hear those words today.

24:17.770 --> 24:19.072
Do not quit that marriage.

24:19.352 --> 24:21.094
Do not quit that job opportunity.

24:21.334 --> 24:22.576
Do not quit that dream.

24:22.856 --> 24:23.497
Keep going.

24:23.697 --> 24:28.482
God's going to give you a fresh pioneer spirit to keep believing and going again.

24:29.143 --> 24:30.584
Pioneers, they take ground.

24:30.605 --> 24:31.706
They refuse to give up.

24:33.988 --> 24:37.893
And I've seen this so many times that every time I settle, I end up with less.

24:42.137 --> 24:42.738
Every time.

24:43.810 --> 24:49.039
In 2026, God has called us to take ground and advance, not retreat.

24:50.421 --> 24:51.823
We've got a city that needs Jesus.

24:54.308 --> 24:58.935
We left on Friday night and we drove home so slowly because we were just overwhelmed with God's goodness.

25:00.318 --> 25:10.034
And I said to Chantel, I said, I am so convinced that there has never been a season in our city where people are ready and ripe to hear the good news of Jesus.

25:11.074 --> 25:17.983
And on Vision Sunday, we're gonna be announcing something that's gonna really spearhead our church in the future, but we are not settling as a church.

25:19.085 --> 25:20.126
We are not settling.

25:20.267 --> 25:21.008
Do not settle.

25:21.248 --> 25:22.950
Do not settle where you are in your marriage.

25:22.970 --> 25:24.753
Do not settle where you are in your business.

25:25.053 --> 25:26.195
Keep moving forward.

25:26.415 --> 25:27.837
God wants to do greater things.

25:27.857 --> 25:30.000
There are greater things ahead for you.

25:31.782 --> 25:33.645
God, give me, come on, let's just say this today.

25:33.725 --> 25:35.427
God, give me a fresh, pioneer spirit.

25:38.892 --> 25:40.274
For some of you, that was difficult.

25:40.834 --> 25:42.817
Because you feel like your age is stopping you.

25:43.397 --> 25:44.378
Maybe there's a book in you.

25:45.340 --> 25:47.623
Maybe you're 18 years young and there's a book in you.

25:48.644 --> 25:50.646
Maybe there's still a discipleship in you.

25:50.666 --> 25:52.268
There's still someone you can mentor.

25:52.288 --> 25:53.430
There's still someone you can help.

25:53.690 --> 25:54.912
There's still someone you can love.

25:55.092 --> 25:58.576
But I want to encourage you do not settle this year in 2026.

25:59.017 --> 26:02.561
Here's the pioneer of our faith.

26:02.581 --> 26:05.045
I'm going to give you some verses for when I feel like settling in 2026.

26:06.166 --> 26:08.108
Luke 11, 9, it says, Jesus speaking.

26:08.529 --> 26:09.330
So I tell you,

26:09.986 --> 26:13.250
Keep on asking and you will receive what you ask.

26:13.590 --> 26:15.572
Keep on seeking and you will find.

26:15.953 --> 26:20.458
Keep on knocking and the door will be opened unto you.

26:21.078 --> 26:26.044
Not settling, asking, not settling, seeking, not settling, knocking.

26:26.324 --> 26:31.470
Jesus said, you've got to keep asking and seeking and knocking in 2026.

26:31.650 --> 26:38.578
Okay, my fourth way I choose to let go of is the pain of rejection.

26:40.930 --> 26:42.632
throw off every weight.

26:45.196 --> 26:47.840
You know, as I'm speaking, I've been speaking about 28 minutes now.

26:48.060 --> 26:48.841
This is getting heavier.

26:50.623 --> 26:51.665
Just breathing a little bit heavier.

26:51.685 --> 26:52.866
I did it the first service as well.

26:52.947 --> 26:54.308
So just bear with me.

26:54.328 --> 26:55.210
But this is getting heavier.

26:56.872 --> 27:00.537
If we don't deal with some of this weight, it sticks.

27:02.420 --> 27:06.505
It's getting harder.

27:06.525 --> 27:09.970
Your rejection is one of the heaviest weights and it's more destructive.

27:10.274 --> 27:11.115
than anything I know.

27:12.257 --> 27:16.965
A hundred positive comments in life can be wiped out with one negative.

27:16.985 --> 27:21.894
We had thousands of people commenting and sending us beautiful emails and letters during the wonder.

27:21.934 --> 27:23.617
It was so encouraging.

27:23.637 --> 27:27.042
In one person, they were walking past me at the wonder at the door.

27:27.744 --> 27:28.986
They said, can you pass it on?

27:29.026 --> 27:30.268
It wasn't as good as last year.

27:34.034 --> 27:36.338
Now, I can be a little bit cheeky,

27:38.946 --> 27:40.728
So I just said, can we give you your money back?

27:41.029 --> 27:41.309
Anyway.

27:45.334 --> 27:55.947
But isn't it amazing how thousands of people, what was the one thing I couldn't get out of my mind over Christmas?

27:57.248 --> 27:59.091
Maybe it wasn't as good, maybe.

28:01.033 --> 28:05.138
And you feel that sense because rejection attaches itself to you.

28:06.530 --> 28:12.559
And when we hear that word, automatically our minds go back to a time, a place, a person where we felt rejected.

28:13.741 --> 28:17.486
Maybe you're rejected in a workplace, maybe you're rejected in a relationship.

28:17.907 --> 28:20.952
Three times my wife, Chantelle, rejected me at Bible school.

28:21.733 --> 28:23.636
She dated her guitar teacher instead.

28:25.378 --> 28:26.500
She said she didn't date him.

28:26.520 --> 28:28.363
She's just a special relationship, just especially.

28:30.566 --> 28:35.954
You know, rejection has a way of destroying a person's life more than anything else.

28:36.482 --> 28:37.243
It can crush us.

28:38.404 --> 28:43.050
The sad fact is that most people watching in the room and online, you've experienced it.

28:43.110 --> 28:44.011
You know what I'm talking about.

28:45.092 --> 28:46.474
And the writer here is challenges.

28:46.514 --> 28:48.697
We've got to drop the weight and walk in freedom.

28:50.459 --> 29:02.894
But as long as you're alive, which pretty much all of you are, as long as you're alive, we're all prone to rejection.

29:04.215 --> 29:06.418
Why does rejection wound us so deeply?

29:06.658 --> 29:07.880
Why does it hurt so much?

29:08.881 --> 29:14.529
Let me explain John 10-10, since the thief comes to rob, to steal, and to destroy.

29:15.491 --> 29:18.735
I have come to give life and life to the full.

29:20.177 --> 29:26.567
Rejection is an anti-Christ spirit, because it's anti the very nature of Christ.

29:27.228 --> 29:30.232
Christ came to bring life and hope and peace into people's life.

29:30.252 --> 29:34.418
The enemy wants to stick shame and rejection on us.

29:34.786 --> 29:38.150
The root of rejection is simply misplaced identity.

29:39.392 --> 29:43.517
If you're constantly feeling rejected, it's because of misplaced identity.

29:43.537 --> 29:51.506
Whenever we base our identity on somebody or something outside of what the word of God says about us, we are prone to rejection.

29:53.308 --> 30:01.638
So when our identity is in what people's comments or people saying how good we are or not, that's where we find our identity, we're prone to rejection.

30:01.698 --> 30:04.722
And it's not rejection that actually shapes our lives.

30:04.802 --> 30:05.703
It's our response.

30:06.724 --> 30:07.444
It's our response.

30:09.807 --> 30:13.610
And the answer to rejection can only be found in Christ.

30:15.412 --> 30:16.773
An ultimate comes down to this.

30:16.933 --> 30:17.694
It's this question.

30:18.335 --> 30:21.578
When I feel rejected, I have to ask myself this one question.

30:22.639 --> 30:24.501
Who do I live my life to please?

30:26.543 --> 30:28.044
Who do I live my life to please?

30:28.985 --> 30:30.807
Am I trying to please everyone with a wonder?

30:31.187 --> 30:32.508
Am I trying to keep everyone happy?

30:33.229 --> 30:34.450
Or ultimately am I trying to

30:34.786 --> 30:35.747
honor and please God.

30:37.028 --> 30:41.232
Once I get that question, I can actually discover my true identity.

30:43.154 --> 30:56.907
Ephesians one versus forces long ago, even before he made the world, God loved us and he chose us in Christ to be holy without fault in his eyes.

30:58.369 --> 31:01.612
If you struggle with rejection, I want you to look at these four truths in this scripture.

31:01.992 --> 31:03.794
Number one is this, God created you.

31:04.866 --> 31:05.427
God created you.

31:05.447 --> 31:06.408
You didn't come from a monkey.

31:07.149 --> 31:07.830
God created you.

31:09.011 --> 31:10.253
You were made in the image of God.

31:11.054 --> 31:11.875
I need to say that again.

31:11.915 --> 31:13.577
You did not come from a chimpanzee.

31:16.721 --> 31:17.662
I'm not an accident.

31:18.183 --> 31:19.084
I'm not a mistake.

31:19.565 --> 31:27.455
I was created in the image of a mighty God and I was fearfully and wonderfully made.

31:28.216 --> 31:29.177
That's my identity.

31:29.537 --> 31:31.480
Number two, number one, he created me.

31:31.520 --> 31:33.202
Number two, he loves me.

31:34.018 --> 31:36.661
Before he made the world, God loves us.

31:36.681 --> 31:39.524
Everyone else might struggle to love me, but he loves me.

31:41.266 --> 31:45.110
Sometimes we're all hard to love at times, but he loves me.

31:46.572 --> 31:54.641
No matter how many mistakes I've made, no matter what I've done, where I've been, I'm here to tell you without a shadow of a doubt, he loves you.

31:56.503 --> 31:58.365
Number three, he chose me.

32:01.228 --> 32:01.849
He chose me.

32:02.089 --> 32:03.090
God loved us.

32:03.202 --> 32:03.983
And chose us.

32:04.744 --> 32:07.046
You might not feel adequate, but God chose you.

32:08.247 --> 32:10.149
Sometimes I don't feel adequate to do what I do.

32:10.169 --> 32:12.791
And I know you don't feel adequate to do what you do, but you know what?

32:12.952 --> 32:13.672
God chose you.

32:15.074 --> 32:16.315
You say, well, I'm not qualified.

32:16.495 --> 32:17.076
It's okay.

32:17.376 --> 32:18.097
God chose you.

32:18.637 --> 32:20.279
He qualifies the unqualified.

32:22.481 --> 32:23.222
God chose you.

32:24.082 --> 32:28.887
Number four, he sees you without fault in his eyes.

32:30.649 --> 32:31.890
That's how God sees you.

32:32.674 --> 32:34.137
You know, this is so relaxing.

32:34.157 --> 32:35.259
This is how God sees me.

32:35.780 --> 32:39.247
He created me, he loves me, and he chose me.

32:40.469 --> 32:43.074
No one else sees me that way on planet Earth, but God does.

32:43.916 --> 32:47.163
So my identity is in Christ.

32:47.183 --> 32:52.032
Young people, you don't have to win the approval of this crazy jack-taught world.

32:52.713 --> 32:55.058
You're already approved by Christ.

32:55.330 --> 33:04.684
No amount of followers, no amount of likes, no amount of people saying this has anything that can change how much God created you, chose you, loved you and sees you.

33:05.586 --> 33:06.848
My identity is in him.

33:06.908 --> 33:08.170
Can we finish off real quickly?

33:08.590 --> 33:09.371
Wait, number five.

33:11.314 --> 33:14.038
The fifth way I choose to let go of is the shame of the past.

33:18.045 --> 33:18.625
Preach it, brother.

33:18.686 --> 33:24.274
He endured the cross.

33:24.802 --> 33:25.563
Scorning.

33:27.064 --> 33:28.926
Scorning, it's shame.

33:30.608 --> 33:34.351
The worst thing in the world is not knowing Jesus.

33:34.892 --> 33:35.492
I'm telling you that now.

33:35.512 --> 33:42.159
If you don't know Jesus, your personal savior, in a few moments, I'm gonna give you an opportunity, because the worst thing in the world is to go through this life without knowing Jesus.

33:42.559 --> 33:50.186
But the second worst thing in the world, hang on, the second thing worst thing in the world is to go through life knowing Jesus, but not enjoying Jesus.

33:52.589 --> 33:54.130
Being a miserable Christian.

33:59.426 --> 34:01.088
You're not, I'll keep you miserable, shame.

34:03.191 --> 34:06.355
It's not that you know that God doesn't love you and you can hear what I have and that's dealt with.

34:07.015 --> 34:13.043
It's simply that you've never dealt with your shame because you're carrying the weight of your past.

34:14.525 --> 34:16.988
How can we enjoy life if we don't like ourselves?

34:20.272 --> 34:22.214
Jesus himself understood shame.

34:22.255 --> 34:25.739
His crucifixion was more than just death.

34:25.859 --> 34:28.242
Romans would crucify Jews naked

34:30.466 --> 34:32.308
There's ultimate humiliation and shame.

34:33.008 --> 34:37.873
And then they placed a sign on top of the cross and said, Jesus, King of the Jews.

34:37.933 --> 34:42.478
What kind of king would be lying naked in front of his own people, dying on a cross?

34:45.561 --> 34:45.921
Shame.

34:48.063 --> 34:49.725
Shame breeds three things in our lives.

34:49.765 --> 34:51.947
Number one, shame breeds fear.

34:53.188 --> 34:55.010
Whenever you feel in shame, you feel fear.

34:55.070 --> 34:57.352
You feel like you'll be exposed or someone will find out.

34:57.392 --> 34:58.994
So you live in fear.

34:59.842 --> 35:01.044
Shame breeds blame.

35:02.325 --> 35:06.130
Whenever we're feeling shame, we want to blame someone else, put it on them for our mistakes.

35:06.170 --> 35:07.291
It was his fault, it was her fault.

35:07.852 --> 35:08.833
So shame breeds blame.

35:08.853 --> 35:12.217
And the third thing that shame does is shame breeds disconnection.

35:14.320 --> 35:16.082
When we feel shame, we want to be disconnected.

35:16.142 --> 35:23.231
The amount of people I know that they leave church because they've made some mistakes and they don't feel like they're good enough to come through the doors.

35:23.632 --> 35:26.015
And we tell you, none of us are good enough to step through those doors.

35:27.597 --> 35:28.658
None of us are good enough.

35:28.994 --> 35:30.536
We all had a bad thought this week.

35:32.279 --> 35:33.040
We've all messed up.

35:33.060 --> 35:34.122
We've all made mistakes.

35:38.709 --> 35:40.993
And Revelation 12, 10 talks about the enemy.

35:41.033 --> 35:43.036
One of Satan's names is accuser.

35:43.377 --> 35:47.443
He says, the accuser of the church and the enemy is constantly trying to accuse us.

35:47.503 --> 35:48.805
You didn't read your Bible this week.

35:48.825 --> 35:49.486
You didn't pray.

35:49.526 --> 35:51.069
You weren't nice to your wife.

35:51.109 --> 35:52.591
You're not really a good Christian.

35:52.611 --> 35:54.354
You could have done better at work.

35:54.882 --> 35:59.227
Are you trying to give up that addiction last year and you failed and the enemy is constantly trying to accuse you?

36:00.348 --> 36:00.909
Constantly.

36:04.533 --> 36:05.894
Isaiah said, do not fear.

36:05.934 --> 36:09.098
If you will not be ashamed, neither be disgraced.

36:09.879 --> 36:15.926
If you will not be put to shame, for you will forget the shame of your youth.

36:17.307 --> 36:20.110
We've got to start forgetting what God's already forgotten.

36:21.732 --> 36:23.474
He endured the cross.

36:24.162 --> 36:26.544
Scorning is shame.

36:27.966 --> 36:31.490
God wants us to drop the weights.

36:34.713 --> 36:37.556
Because we might start off this year strong and think we can do it.

36:37.576 --> 36:45.023
We had a good recharge over Christmas New Year, but the reality is we never dealt with the stuff, the rejection, the control, the fear.

36:45.624 --> 36:46.705
We never actually dealt with it.

36:47.586 --> 36:51.410
We just ate and feel good and now we think we can keep going, but God's saying no.

36:52.834 --> 36:54.717
You know, vulnerability breaks the weight.

36:56.179 --> 37:00.785
We got, wow.

37:00.805 --> 37:02.127
Do you know how free in this feels?

37:03.288 --> 37:04.590
And I'm not just saying that it really does.

37:08.315 --> 37:13.342
Lay aside every weight.

37:14.884 --> 37:19.510
They're so easily entangles us and let us run.

37:20.732 --> 37:22.354
Come on, we're going to run through this year.

37:23.138 --> 37:27.204
Let us run the race that has been marked out for us.

37:29.747 --> 37:31.450
You know, the devil hates this stuff.

37:32.531 --> 37:37.298
When we expose this, we expose him because he's the father of lies.

37:39.681 --> 37:41.744
And you've ever heard it's dead weight.

37:41.784 --> 37:45.109
That term, it can be dead weight today.

37:46.431 --> 37:48.754
You can leave it at the foot of the cross.

37:53.954 --> 37:59.540
I'm gonna finish with this, but God wants to remind you again today that you're forgiven.

38:00.562 --> 38:04.927
Forgiven of the challenges, the fears, the rejection, forgiven free.

38:07.129 --> 38:11.234
My favorite scripture in the whole Bible is Lamentations 3.22.

38:12.616 --> 38:14.918
It's probably not a day that I don't say it at some point.

38:15.559 --> 38:19.524
The steadfast love of the Lord never ceases.

38:20.785 --> 38:21.586
His mercy,

38:22.786 --> 38:23.868
never comes to an end.

38:25.210 --> 38:27.153
It is new every morning.

38:27.974 --> 38:30.478
Great is your faithfulness.

38:32.321 --> 38:35.606
God's love and forgiveness towards us, it never ends.

38:36.668 --> 38:43.038
Do you know what, for many years I actually struggled with why would God keep wanting to forgive me when I keep messing up?

38:44.680 --> 38:48.306
Because you might mess up in marriage once or twice and then it's over.

38:48.802 --> 38:51.846
You might mess up at work and you might get a warning and then it's over.

38:52.167 --> 38:56.552
You might mess up with a friend, you might let them down and they get rid of you.

38:56.572 --> 39:02.360
So why does God keep forgiving me even when I keep failing him, even when I keep messing up?

39:07.347 --> 39:11.433
And this is what he showed me because he wants relationship with me.

39:12.714 --> 39:14.477
Why does Chantal keep forgiving me?

39:15.638 --> 39:18.482
Because her desire for relationships

39:18.562 --> 39:20.404
is stronger than my mistakes.

39:21.947 --> 39:28.295
Whenever your desire for relationship is stronger than a person's mistakes, a relationship can be restored.

39:29.597 --> 39:37.527
And do you know what God's desire for relationship with you and me is stronger and greater than every single one of our mistakes?

39:38.108 --> 39:45.458
That's why His mercy is new every morning, because He desires relationship with us.

39:48.642 --> 39:50.744
So I'm not defined by the weight.

39:52.046 --> 39:53.147
I'm defined by his love.

39:54.509 --> 39:55.770
I'm a new creation today.

39:55.810 --> 39:59.414
This year, I'm completing him.

40:00.676 --> 40:01.657
I'm a child of God.

40:02.778 --> 40:05.121
I'm alive in Christ.

40:06.162 --> 40:09.326
I am free from the law of sin and death.

40:10.487 --> 40:13.891
I'm the righteousness of God in Christ Jesus.

40:14.672 --> 40:15.973
Does it mean I've not got a past?

40:16.114 --> 40:16.434
No.

40:16.706 --> 40:18.068
Does it mean I've not got mistakes?

40:18.188 --> 40:18.388
No.

40:18.629 --> 40:20.452
Does it mean I don't feel rejection or fear?

40:20.472 --> 40:24.818
None of those things is just that I know who I am in Christ.

40:25.960 --> 40:26.981
Amen.

40:27.001 --> 40:33.871
Amen.

40:33.891 --> 40:35.393
I want everyone just to close their eyes.

40:35.454 --> 40:36.976
No one moving around.

40:38.398 --> 40:40.281
Because I want to talk about the greatest weight of all.

40:40.301 --> 40:41.202
It's the weight of sin.

40:43.874 --> 40:46.617
Sin is the only thing that can separate us from God.

40:50.622 --> 40:53.906
Today the Bible says we've all sinned, we've all fallen short of the glory of God.

40:53.926 --> 40:54.888
We've all got this wrong.

40:55.649 --> 40:59.754
We've all tried to walk, do life our own way in our own time.

41:00.815 --> 41:02.537
God is saying today, friend, I love you.

41:03.038 --> 41:05.781
Maybe you came to the wonder or you came to bed grills.

41:06.762 --> 41:13.010
You came back today because you're searching for meaning, you're searching for direction and purpose for your life because this world is offering you very little.

41:14.306 --> 41:17.991
Today you can find that his name is Jesus.

41:18.011 --> 41:21.976
You say, well, I don't understand it or nor do I really, but I do know that he loves me.

41:22.717 --> 41:23.619
He's got a plan for me.

41:23.939 --> 41:24.920
He's got a future for me.

41:26.883 --> 41:29.927
And today the Father wants to wrap his loving arms around you.

41:30.808 --> 41:36.997
Say to you, you could make it, but it begins with a decision to say, Jesus, I want to follow you.

41:38.639 --> 41:41.042
Maybe you once walked with God, but you've drifted away.

41:41.794 --> 41:45.060
Maybe once had a relationship, but life's taken you down a different path.

41:45.621 --> 41:47.705
You've been through some challenging times.

41:48.687 --> 41:49.949
God says, I still love you.

41:50.771 --> 41:54.097
My desire for you is greater than your mistakes.

41:55.159 --> 41:56.742
That's why my love is here today.

41:58.825 --> 42:03.474
Right now, if you say, John, I want to become a Christian or I want to come back to God.

42:04.130 --> 42:07.555
All I want you to do right now, all over this room is say, John, I need Jesus.

42:07.595 --> 42:09.758
Just slip up your hand right now and say, John, pray for me.

42:09.818 --> 42:10.699
Lift it up nice and high.

42:10.940 --> 42:11.701
John, pray for me.

42:12.001 --> 42:13.103
All over this room, lift it up.

42:13.163 --> 42:13.744
God bless you.

42:14.104 --> 42:14.705
God bless you.

42:14.986 --> 42:15.526
God bless you.

42:15.586 --> 42:16.147
God bless you.

42:16.207 --> 42:16.768
God bless you.

42:17.209 --> 42:18.250
God bless you.

42:18.471 --> 42:19.011
God bless you.

42:19.592 --> 42:20.554
Lift it up nice and high.

42:21.034 --> 42:21.996
I need Jesus today.

42:22.016 --> 42:23.157
I need Jesus.

42:24.699 --> 42:25.280
God bless you.

42:25.761 --> 42:26.322
God bless you.

42:26.422 --> 42:26.983
God bless you.

42:27.023 --> 42:27.544
God bless you.

42:28.144 --> 42:29.326
All right, here's what I want us to do.

42:29.346 --> 42:32.050
I want us all to stand, but before we do,

42:32.258 --> 42:35.702
When we stand, if you lifted up your hand, I would love you just to come out the front.

42:35.722 --> 42:36.683
I wanna pray for you.

42:37.023 --> 42:38.084
I'm gonna shake your hand.

42:38.365 --> 42:39.326
I wanna pray for you.

42:39.446 --> 42:43.230
And we're gonna pray that God's love will come and fall on you in this moment.

42:43.250 --> 42:44.471
So let's all stand to our feet.

42:44.711 --> 42:48.516
If you lifted up your hand, even if you didn't, you say, I wanna become a Christian right now.

42:48.776 --> 42:49.517
Come on, you come.

42:49.897 --> 42:50.738
You come right now.

42:51.299 --> 42:52.280
We'll wait for you.

42:52.660 --> 42:53.361
We'll wait for you.

42:53.381 --> 42:53.861
You come.

42:54.442 --> 42:55.563
Come to Jesus today.

42:56.124 --> 42:57.125
He's waiting for you.

42:57.265 --> 42:57.746
You come.

43:00.388 --> 43:01.810
You come to Jesus.

43:05.762 --> 43:13.629
We're gonna say a prayer right now and I wanna congratulate you for this courage that you've shown to step out of your seat and follow Jesus.

43:14.190 --> 43:15.231
He loves you so much.

43:16.032 --> 43:17.593
I don't know your story, but he does.

43:18.654 --> 43:19.935
He says, I forgive you today.

43:20.956 --> 43:22.798
So let's say this prayer out loud.

43:23.719 --> 43:27.182
Father God, thank you for dying for me.

43:28.684 --> 43:31.006
To forgive all my sins and failures.

43:33.328 --> 43:35.250
I believe that you rose from the dead.

43:36.674 --> 43:38.657
so that I can have a brand new life.

43:40.439 --> 43:53.817
Please come into my heart and help me by the power of the Holy Spirit to trust and to live for you.

43:53.837 --> 43:54.018
Amen.

43:54.038 --> 43:54.238
Amen.

43:54.258 --> 43:55.620
Can we congratulate everyone?

43:59.845 --> 44:01.187
Now we've got a little gift for you.

44:01.207 --> 44:03.791
It's Mark's gospel.

44:04.332 --> 44:06.194
This is Ian and Gemma over here.

44:06.434 --> 44:08.797
We're just going to get this a little chap or it's a little bit quiet.

44:08.817 --> 44:11.460
We're going to give you that, give you some information about your next steps.

44:12.101 --> 44:13.643
And this isn't the end, it's the beginning.

44:14.103 --> 44:15.905
I'm going to come down and shake your hand as well.

44:15.965 --> 44:21.632
And we're going to celebrate this new chapter as you drop the greatest weight of all and leave it here today.

44:21.672 --> 44:22.033
Amen.

44:22.253 --> 44:24.095
Come on, let's congratulate and sing along.

44:28.380 --> 44:29.842
Thanks again for tuning in.

44:30.242 --> 44:38.134
If you said yes to Jesus today by saying the Salvation Prayer, we'd love for you to email connections at soulchurch.com.

44:38.154 --> 44:42.741
So we can talk to you a little bit more about this incredible decision you've just made.

44:43.362 --> 44:51.815
And if at any point in the service, you felt moved to give towards any of our local or global initiatives, head to soulchurch.com.

44:51.835 --> 44:58.866
And don't forget to stay connected with us on Facebook, Instagram, and YouTube by searching at soulchurch.uk.

44:59.138 --> 45:00.690
Take care and God bless.

